00:13:34.720 --> 00:13:42.190
So, this comes from clustering.
Is that legible?

00:13:42.190 --> 00:13:45.789
Close enough.
Okay.

00:13:45.789 --> 00:13:48.843
And so, the great thing about
this was, if you will recall,

00:13:48.843 --> 00:13:51.843
that there were three different
lines on a two-dimensional

00:13:51.843 --> 00:13:54.283
graph,
and they all cross at the same

00:13:54.283 --> 00:13:56.140
point.
And this constitutes a test of

00:13:56.140 --> 00:13:59.008
the theory, because it is not
necessarily true that if you put

00:13:59.008 --> 00:14:01.923
down three lines at random in a
two-dimensional space that they

00:14:01.923 --> 00:14:03.710
will all cross at the same
point.

00:14:03.710 --> 00:14:07.489
And so, the fact that they do
makes you think that something

00:14:07.489 --> 00:14:11.269
about how we understand what's
going on is going pretty much

00:14:11.269 --> 00:14:13.783
right.
Because there's no reason for

00:14:13.783 --> 00:14:15.980
these things to cross at a
point.

00:14:15.980 --> 00:14:18.988
We predict that they do because
you know they're all measuring

00:14:18.988 --> 00:14:21.059
the same Universe but in
different ways.

00:14:21.059 --> 00:14:26.147
And so, the fact that they do
lend some credence to this whole

00:14:26.147 --> 00:14:30.009
wonderful set of stories.
But there's another way of

00:14:30.009 --> 00:14:33.167
